latestIgtvVideos.caption:
MINE- Campaign Film
.
Music by @whenchaimettoast
.
All parents are enthusiastic and emotional about the birth and growth of their children. - the journey, growth, details- everything is documented and is equally important & special!
To materialise this emotion and experience, I've designed a modernised gender-neutral freesize bib-to be worn over any garment of one's choice- , with direct symbolisms from one's personal stories. 

Each stuffed mini shape , has a significance, they're a representation of various little milestones and "firsts" In a child's journey- 
First having the date of birth 
Second , the initials 
Third, the place of birth
Fourth, their first word
Fifth, baby's first house number and so on. 

With a motive to be able to wear your baby's story & your parental journey close to your heart.
With direct symbolisms and references to the details , the bib doesn't JUST remain a "bib", it's your story, your journey, your emotion & your baby in a garment. 

Love, mine.
.
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
Styled my first show, and @iak, celebrating 5 fabulous years of @snbyshantanunikhil and 25 years of @lakmefashionwk @fdciofficial 🧿
When we saw the final collection, i instantly knew the direction would need to be clean, chic and minimal- letting the clothes and prints shine! Using tone on tone ties, print on print scarves, statement eyewear, the brand's signature brooches, shoes and bags, and chanelling a gender fluid zone for girls was the mood and zone we wanted to go for! @sublimesound__ on music, the incredible @lubna.adam choreographing and @danielcbauer for HMU - I couldn't have asked for a better first!
Most of all, @nikhil1975 and Shantnu for trusting me and my vision for this momentous show, and just the constant encouragement- truly meant the world.
My right hand gal @sherylkhurana and @vaishnaviiiiii23 @deardarsshan the most adorb team - the entire sn team , much love!
Hugs kisses love.

latestPosts.caption:
The past couple of weeks have honestly been such a refreshing change- much needed down time!
I’ve been doing all the things I’ve been meaning to try or get back to—pottery, rock climbing, hot yoga, getting into fitness, starting a skincare routine, eating cleaner, drinking better… just taking better care of myself, inside and out.

As someone in a creative field, we’re constantly on the go-coming up with ideas, building, creating. But I’ve realised how important it is to slow down and make time for yourself. To try new things, to move your body, to spend time with people who matter, and just... be.

Take that time out for yourself🤍🧿🪄
